snippet.textDisplay:
I got caught on the roof once at around the same age goofing around and sense I live in the country a hop down was NOT an option but for a different reason. The day before it might as well went Noah's ark [Dunno how I didn't just slip off] but due to the caverns below me and the clay soil if I jumped, I would need a second party to pull me out of the ground looney toons style.

Eventually your boy saw no other choice so I jumped for it and so soon as I did I was waste deep in wet clay on an overcast day. I ended up screaming at the top 9f my lungs and my neighbors boys around my age pulled me out [without my pants and knee high mud boots] so I grabbed those as quick as possible but the damage was done my caramel skin was a deep crimson and they just looked at me like "Damn I feel bad for you."


You may wonder where my foljs were? This was one of my first times home alone while they sat out to get groceries and your maun man here went on the roof to fetch a baseball.

Their was no not telling my mother as a perfect me sized hole was next to my grandmothers flower bed and yeah my Grandma slapped a couple times but I didn't get grounded because my Mom flat out said "What can I do to you that is worse than what you just did to yourself?"

It ended up raining for like 2 days an hour after I got outta the hole but that experience will forever stick with me
